Durban - A 17-year-old teenage boy drowned while swimming at an excavation site Hazlemere Road near Mhlasini in Verulam on Saturday. At noon, Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa) was called to the scene by the public after the teenger was dragged out of the water by one of his friends. “Upon arrival the teenager was assessed by medics. He showed no signs of life and was declared deceased at the scene,” said Prem Balram, Rusa spokesperson. He said it is alleged that the teenger lived in Ndwedwe with an aunt. He was visiting his mother and stepfather for the long weekend. “He and four other boys aged between eight and 18 decided to swim in the excavation site that filled up with water over a period of time. While swimming he started experiencing difficulty resulting in him drowning,” Balram said. He said the teeneager’s family has been told about his death. Police could not be reached at the time of publication. Daily News